    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<blockquote><p>In 1947 Life Magazine asked some famous comic strip artists to to draw their famous characters while wearing a blindfold. The results are interesting.</p></blockquote>

<p><img src="https://farm4.staticflickr.com/3929/15372365536_892afa7e19_o.gif" alt="Steve Canyon" /></p>

<p>It definitely gives a new meaning to the phrase: &ldquo;I could do that with my eyes closed&rdquo;.</p>

<p>Via <a href="http://www.messynessychic.com/2014/09/29/13-things-i-found-on-the-internet-today-vol-xciii/">Messy Nessy Chic</a>.</p>
